				<p>Good observation, Scott. I&#8217;m hoping to cover that technique in a future article. :) </p>
<p>I personally rarely use that technique, however, because I don&#8217;t tend to think of my websites as organized according to typography vs. layout. I see a &#8220;sidebar&#8221; (for example) as a cohesive unit, with its own layout and typographical considerations. I quickly get annoyed when I want to bump up a header size by a few percentage points and move it by a couple of pixels, and that requires me to edit more than one style sheet.</p>
